 But how do you account for people who find religion NOT seeking a cause?

 Also, your model only assumes that religion has to be juxtaposed to empirical and observable causes, being substituted for them by it's non-empirical nature. But many scientists throughout history have had no problem reconciling religion and the empirical--in fact to a number of them, the two were complemetary. The idea that they can only be juxtaposed seems like an unproven premise to me.
